BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:BzORpWf204faw8EUPi-Gf
SUMMARY:Destination Roadhouse -- Jazz Jam Night
DTSTAMP:20260318T153724Z
DTSTART:20260325T020000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us every Tuesday night for **The Roadhouse Jazz Jam**\, wh
	ere the city’s best musicians — and brave newcomers — come together to cel
	ebrate the spirit of live jazz.\n\nBring your instrument\, your voice\, or
	 just your love for great music. The night starts with a house band set\, 
	then the stage opens up for an unforgettable jam session filled with swing
	\, soul\, and spontaneity.\n\n🎵 Smooth vibes • 🎺 Live improvisation\n\nCom
	e play\, listen\, and feel the groove — the Tuesday Jazz Jam is where the 
	magic happens.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/destinatio
	n-roadhouse-jazz-jam-night/18285728/2026-03-24T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts 
	& Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/destination-roadhouse-jaz
	z-jam-night/18285728/2026-03-24T00
LOCATION:The Roadhouse\, 19955 28th Ave S\, SeaTac\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TTpYC3rc4I29fCzvlhImE
SUMMARY:IMPROV 100 TUESDAY -  Intro to Improv: Say Yes!\, SPRING'26
DTSTAMP:20260318T153724Z
DTSTART:20260325T020000Z
DESCRIPTION:Say yes! Learn to listen\, connect\, play and use your own life
	 to create stories with others! An 8 week intro to improvised theatre! Dis
	cover Unexpected Productions' philosophy of improvisation\, developed over
	 our 43 years of improvising in Seattle! You'll learn how to actively list
	en\, to use your own life to create collaborative stories\, and you'll wor
	k on the fundamental principles of improvisation: what it means to say\, "
	Yes\, And"\, how to tell stories that include everyone in the room\, how t
	o stop worrying about failing\, and the games and concepts behind what we 
	do on stages around the world! Under the guidance of one of our best Seatt
	le improv teachers\, you will learn to:· -Be a Better Listener -Conquer Fe
	ars -Spark Creativity -Meet New People & Make New Friends -Become a Better
	 Problem Solver -Gain Confidence· -Fail With Grace \\(and Maybe Even Enjoy
	 It\\) -Say Yes More in Your Life -Get Out of Your Comfort Zone -Become a 
	Better Public Speaker -Discover More About Yourself -...and have a blast d
	oing it! Time and Dates : Tuesdays for eight \\(8\\) weeks\, from March 24
	 to May 22\, 7pm to 9:30pm NOTE: Attendance at the first session of your c
	ourse is mandatory as it sets the agenda for the entire quarter. If you th
	ink you will have to miss the first class\, please consider registering fo
	r the next quarter. No Prerequisites. All students begin at this level\, e
	ven those with existing improv experience. It’s a prerequisite to the othe
	r levels. Location: 5700 6th Ave St\, Suite 109\, Umbrella Room\, Seattle\
	, WA 98108 \\(In Georgetown\, south of downtown\, with plenty of parking.\
	\) Maximum Students: 16 Cost: Ticket price $295.00 Age: 18 and above \\*\\
	*Cancellation policy: If you must cancel before the first class\, we can o
	nly offer credit towards the same level class next quarter. We are unable 
	to offer refunds. If you cancel after the first class we cannot offer cred
	it towards a future class. Again\, we are unable to offer refunds.\n\nhttp
	s://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/improv-100-tuesday-intro-to-impr
	ov-say-yes-spring-26/18291137/2026-03-24T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Cult
	ure
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/improv-100-tuesday-intro-
	to-improv-say-yes-spring-26/18291137/2026-03-24T00
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:h7hrpLKHgtYX8zXVi0zWx
SUMMARY:Chuckle Bucket Tuesday @ Club Comedy Seattle (Open Mic)
DTSTAMP:20260318T153724Z
DTSTART:20260325T020000Z
DESCRIPTION:Club Comedy Seattle hosts Chuckle Bucket Tuesday each week. The
	 luck of the bucket rules the night. Comics drop their name in and hope to
	 be drawn for one of the spots on the list to tell jokes. It's fun\, fast-
	paced and will keep you laughing hard on your Tuesday night.\n\nDoor 7:00P
	M/Show 7:30PM\n\nAdmission: $7 \\+ $0.35 City Of Seattle Admission Tax\n\n
	21\\+ With Valid ID REQUIRED for entry. NO REFUNDS.\n\nFYI: If you have a 
	large party it's easier for us to seat you all together if you purchase al
	l the tickets under one name.\n\n.\n\nClub Comedy Seattle FAQ\n\nIs there 
	an age/ID requirement?\n\nYes. We are strictly 21\\+ and valid physical ID
	 is REQUIRED For Entry\n\nIs Seating First Come/First Served?\n\nYes. The 
	room is all two top tables and we seat guests in the order in which they a
	rrive.\n\nCan I reserve a table for a group?\n\nWe do not take reservation
	s for tables\, but groups can arrive early to secure seating together.\n\n
	Are tickets available at the door if an event is sold out online?\n\nIf an
	 event is sold out online there are no tickets available at the door.\n\nW
	hat are the club’s hours of operation?\n\nThe club is open Tuesday to Sund
	ay. Doors open a half hour before each show.\n\nWhat is the Parking like?\
	n\nGenerally there is street parking available in the blocks surrounding t
	he club. There are also affordable parking lots on 16th Ave E right around
	 the block from the club along with other easy options in the neighborhood
	\n\nIs there a dress code?\n\nThere is no formal dress code\, but we recom
	mend smart casual attire.\n\nCan I bring food or drinks?\n\nOutside food a
	nd drinks are not allowed. We have a full bar and a menu available for you
	r enjoyment.\n\nWhat if I can't make it and need to cancel my ticket?\n\nA
	ll ticket sales are final. However\, if you can’t make it\, please contact
	 us through Eventbrite in advance\, and we’ll do our best to accommodate y
	ou.\n\nWill there be an opener for the headliner?\n\nYes\, headliner shows
	 feature a lineup of comedians\, including a host\, an opener\, and the he
	adliner.\n\nWill the comics talk to me like I see in online videos all the
	 time?\n\nMost likely they won't. Crowd work videos are popular for postin
	g online\, but crowd work doesn't generally happen at the online frequency
	 in live comedy show situations. Some comics do engage the crowd as part o
	f their regular set and it's generally always fun and more about making fu
	n of themselves than making fun of the crowd.\n\nHow can I get on the Chea
	p Laughs Open Mic On Wednesdays?\n\nSubmissions for spots on the Wednesday
	 Cheap Laughs Open Mic are accepted only on the Tuesday before between 12:
	00AM and 11:59PM via email at openmic@clubcomedyseattle.com\n\nDo you offe
	r group discounts?\n\nYes\, we offer discounts for groups of ten or more. 
	Please contact us for more details.\n\nCan I meet the comedians after the 
	show?\n\nMeet-and-greet opportunities vary by event. Please ask staff for 
	details after the show.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/c
	huckle-bucket-tuesday-club-comedy-seattle-open-mic/18244225/2026-03-24T00\
	n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/chuckle-bucket-tuesday-cl
	ub-comedy-seattle-open-mic/18244225/2026-03-24T00
LOCATION:Club Comedy Seattle\, 328 15th Ave E\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H30M
END:VEVENT
